==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro}} {{term|conceler||hide, disguise|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|concelare|concelāre|Lang=la}}, infinitive of {{term|concelo|concelō|carefully disguise|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-conceal.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|iːl}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To hide something from [[view]] or from public [[knowledge]], to try to keep something [[secret]].
#: ''He tried to '''conceal''' the truth about his [[health]].''

====Related terms====
* [[concealing]], [[concealed]]

====Synonyms====
* [[hide]]
* [[obfuscate]]
* [[secrete]]

====Antonyms====
* [[reveal]]
* [[uncover]]
* [[admit]]

